Ignoring the illogical bards, etc, out there, the CON of the pet means nothing to me, (it's an NPC!  Helloooo!  Remember that green con giant on the Kromrif Military Leggings quest when you were lower level?  You, like everyone else said, bah, it's green....HOLY CRAP!  NUKE NUKE!  Hehehe) and escaped my notice for a long time till a guildy brought it to my attention. I use the epic and prefer the epic even in PoS against any non-giant-class mob because the kills are still faster! I know that's a horrible thing to say...and have NO idea why that would anger someone , but think about it. The mage epic is arguably the hardest of the epic-quests. I think this is Verants way of not entirely invalidating the quest. I think it was very well done that the epic and each of the 4 61+ pets each have their own advantages and none of them invalidates another. Now a mage has Five pets to choose from, instead of four. Pretty cool I think. I have read 4 parse tests to date, 3 I think on this board, all of which confirm the epics better dps (I've yet to see a test in high tier planes, maybe because these mages there have the high end focus gloves and therefore are on a completly different page, and don't care a wet slap about any of this. But I suspect the results will be similar...or not...don't freak). Get over it, and enjoy the advantage we've been given. . . and if you're a biased naysayer or bard who retired their mage...go get you mage out of the closet, get an epic and see for yourself. Your views would then be given much more validity. And if your a rogue or something complaining that we are just too powerful as a result of all this (hehe)...bring it up with Verant. We're (well, most of us) are okay with it.  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=163088"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.attbi.com"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCO