<br>
the main issue i have with your points is that there is a line that has to be drawn between 'situationally useful' and 'so situational it is never used'<br>
<br>
for a lot of people, at 65, for real xp camps...it means nothing to say the epic is better on mobs under 60 in old world.  for the simple reason that they are fighting 62+ in pop.  the epic pet is useful in certain situations, i won't argue that.  however, i feel that the epic pet is NOT useful to the majority of L65 xp-group magicians out there, simply because they don't find themselves in those situations with any regularity.<br>
<br>
from my expierience..<br>
farming greens for an item: epic<br>
soloing lt blues when bored: epic<br>
xp group on L62+ mobs: water<br>
duo/trio with pet tanking L62+ mobs: air<br>
<br>
i know where most of my time is spent, and it's not farming or soloing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 3009<br> <font color=#333333>(3/1/03 12:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8858.topic&index=134>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet Parse, Low AC, Spell immune mob.  Epic Vs 61 Air</span><hr size=1> This thread was useful because at minimum, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Eandori</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and others like myself learned in detail considerations that effect the taking and interpretation of parses.<br>
